3. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The safe set problem has applications in game theory, as it can be used to model the concept of a coalition in cooperative games. 
4. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper uses techniques from discrete mathematics, such as graph theory and combinatorics, to study the safe set problem.
